# tkv2 — offline primitives (localStorage, onlineSignal, persistedSignal)

Slice `tkv2-offline` of `specs/ssc-toolkit-v2.md`. Off-browser both lanes run
localStorage over a per-process map and report online — the same code drives
real `localStorage`/`navigator.onLine` in the browser.

[localStorageGet, localStorageSet, localStorageRemove, onlineSignal, persistedSignal](std/ui/offline.ssc)

```scalascript
// Storage round-trip, including the missing-key shape.
println(localStorageGet("missing"))
localStorageSet("k1", "v1")
println(localStorageGet("k1"))
localStorageRemove("k1")
println(localStorageGet("k1"))

// Online state: constant true off-browser (JVM interpreter and Node alike).
val online = onlineSignal()
println(online())

// persistedSignal: default when nothing stored…
val p1 = persistedSignal("draft", "empty")
println(p1())

// …write-back on set (observable via raw storage)…
p1.set("hello")
println(localStorageGet("draft"))

// …and a later signal for the same key initializes from storage.
val p2 = persistedSignal("draft", "empty")
println(p2())

// Pre-seeded storage wins over the default.
localStorageSet("lang", "pl")
val lang = persistedSignal("lang", "en")
println(lang())
```
